'''Yakov Lazarevich Geronimus''', sometimes spelled '''J. Geronimus''' ({{lang-ru|Я́ков Лазаре́вич Геро́нимус}}; February 6, 1898, [[Rostov]] &ndash; July 17, 1984, [[Kharkov]]) was a Russian mathematician known for contributions to [[theoretical mechanics]] and the study of [[orthogonal polynomials]]. The [[Geronimus polynomials]] are named after him.

